# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----   Limiting the subject line to 50 characters.  --->|
#
# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try to limit each line to a maximum of 72 characters.   --->|
#
# Provide links or keys to any relevant ticket/issue/PR
#
# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   refactor (refactoring code)
#   style    (formatting, missing semicolons, etc)
#   docs     (changes to documentation)
#   test     (adding or refactoring tests)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   ci       (CI/CD configuration)
#   chore    (dependency updates, tool config)
#
# Scope can be:
#   books      (book catalog features)
#   issues     (book issue/checkout features)
#   members    (member management)
#   fines      (charge/fine administration)
#   reports    (reporting and analytics)
#   inventory  (copy/inventory tracking)
#   ui         (user interface)
#   api        (API endpoints)
#   db         (database/migrations)
#   auth       (authentication/authorization)
#
# Subject line imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
# Do not include the issue number in the subject
# Do not end subject line with a period
#
# Body should explain what and why, not how
# Each line max 72 chars (except for long URLs)
# Separate subject from body with a blank line
#
# Footer area for issue references:
# References: #123
# Closes: #456
# Breaking-Change: description of breaking change
# --- END COMMIT MESSAGE TEMPLATE ---
